<1ST_LINE>r a AM-People     10-23 0823</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-People,0852</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>People in the News</HEAD>
<HEAD>LaserPhoto NY44</HEAD>
<DATELINE>OAKLAND, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Rock musician Eddie Money said he's sold
5 million records and has little to show for it, but he hopes he's
winning his battles with drugs and alcohol.
   In an interview published Sunday in The Tribune of Oakland, the
39-year-old Money discussed his tumultuous life.
   ``Nobody's stealing from me. But I get tired of being the only
rock star shopping at Miller's Outpost,'' he said. ``I guess it's a
step up from K mart, where I used to get my clothes.''
   By his own count, he's been clean of drugs and booze since
shortly before his daughter Jessica's birth six months ago and
finds he sings better straight.
   ``Besides, I didn't want to be a stoned father raising a kid,
you know?'' he said.
   Money is known for such hits as ``Take Me Home Tonight,'' ``Baby
Hold On,'' and ``Walk on Water.'' But his struggles with drugs and
drink haven't been easy, and he says it's one reason he's living in
Los Angeles right now rather than the Bay area.
   ``I'm trying to stay away from my old crowd where it's easy to
get that stuff,'' he said. ``I'm just a guy with no control. I plan
to make it this time.''
</TEXT>
<DATELINE>ADELAIDE, Australia (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The Duke and Duchess of York played a
game of hide and seek with reporters Sunday, the last day of their
informal visit to this city.
   Australian Associated Press reported that Andrew and his wife,
the former Sarah Ferguson, spent the day at a private home in the
Adelaide Hills after an elaborate escape from the city to avoid the
media.
   Reporters admitted being fooled by decoys and a change of cars,
getting lost in a high-speed cat and mouse game along the freeway
into the hills. However, one TV station that had been tipped off
managed to find the couple at their secret location.
   Despite rumors that they were to make appearances at formal
functions, the two have kept a low profile in Adelaide.
   After their outing Sunday, the royal couple were to return to
the ship H.M.S. Edinburgh, which is scheduled to leave Monday
morning with the Duke, a crew member. The Duchess is expected to
meet up with him again in the West Australian capital of Perth on
Friday.
</TEXT>
<DATELINE>OAK PARK, Ill. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Actress Marlo Thomas says she believes
giving birth should be a ``real family experience,'' and that's why
she was at a suburban hospital to help dedicate its new birthing
center.
   The West Suburban Hospital Medical Center tries to bring a
home-style atmosphere to the hospital _ if your home has designer
wallpaper, carpeting and retracting operating room lights.
   ``I'm glad to see maternity care catching up with the 21st
century and to make giving birth a real family experience,'' Ms.
Thomas said.
   Hospital spokeswoman Amy Lively said the center, similar to many
others at the country but billed as the first of its kind in the
Chicago area, marks an end to ``shuttle maternity'' in which the
woman checks into the labor room, then is taken to the delivery
room, and then on to the recovery room.
   At the center, all the stages of childbirth are accomplished in
a single-patient suite, with everything designed to make delivery
less stressful. Medical equipment is hidden away when not needed,
and family members can be on hand.
</TEXT>
<DATELINE>NEW ORLEANS (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   It was a wedding of two second-generation
government officials as State Treasurer Mary Landrieu married Frank
Snellings, a fellow Democratic politician.
   Landrieu, daughter of former U.S. Housing and Urban Development
Secretary and New Orleans Mayor Moon Landrieu, was married Saturday
at the uptown Roman Catholic church that serves her parents'
neighborhood.
   Landrieu, one of nine children of the former mayor, was elected
state treasurer in 1987 after seven years in Louisiana's House of
Representatives, during which she took strong stands on issues
involving women and children. She also is a real estate developer.
   Snellings was elected in 1979 to the Ouachita Parish Police Jury
and is its past president. A police jury is the equivalent of a
county commission. His mother, Mary Louise Snellings, is a member
of the state's board of education.
</TEXT>
<DATELINE>PALMA DE MAJORCA, Balearic Islands, (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Queen Elizabeth II
cruised the Mediterranean waters off the Spanish island of Majorca
on Sunday, the second day of a two-day private visit in Spain.
   She and her husband, Prince Philip, also left the royal yacht
Britannia to visit the Spanish royal couple, Juan Carlos and Sofia,
on the Spanish royal yacht Fortuna. Both yachts headed for the tiny
island of Cabrera.
   The British couple arrived in Palma after a five-day state visit
to Spain, which ended Friday in Barcelona. It was the first state
visit ever to Spain by a reigning British monarch.
   Elizabeth and Philip were to return to London by air Monday.
</TEXT>
