<HEAD>Greek Composer Suffers Heart Attack</HEAD>
<DATELINE>OSTEND, Belgium (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Mikis Theodorakis, a Greek musician and a
political leader, has suffered a heart attack, organizers of his
Belgian tour reported Sunday.
   They said he was taken to a hospital in Antwerp after he was
stricken Saturday in the port city of Ostend and his condition was
not life threatening.
   The 63-year-old musician is one of Greece's most popular
composers and singers. He also is known for his political career
and opposition to the military dictatorship that ruled from 1967-74.
   Elected as a communist member of Parliament, he was jailed for
three years but freed in 1970 under international pressure. After
exile in France he returned to Greece in 1974. He was re-elected to
Parliament in 1981.
   Theodorakis was on a nine-day tour of Belgium and his last
concert, which was canceled, had been been scheduled for Saturday
in Ostend.
