<1ST_LINE>r a AM-GirlFound     10-23 0203</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Girl Found,0210</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Ohio Teen Found After Six-Year Search</HEAD>
<DATELINE>HUNTINGTON BEACH, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   An Ohio girl who disappeared six
years ago was found in an apartment in this Los Angeles area
community, and her grandfather was arrested for questioning, police
said.
   Charity Freeman, 13, of Toledo, was discovered Friday when
detectives went to see her grandfather about an automobile
repossession, said Lt. John Foster.
   The girl answered the door, he said.
   Leroy Freeman was arrested for investigation of kidnapping and
unlawful flight to avoid prosecution, Foster said.
   ``Thank goodness, this may finally be coming to an end,'' said
Victor J. Gonzalez, an attorney for the girl's mother, Karen
Creswell. ``It's been a long, long ordeal.''
   The girl was abducted in September 1982. Freeman and his
daughter had apparently argued over how Charity should be raised.
   The case gained national attention in 1985 when it was rumored
that Freeman was connected to a satanic cult in northern Ohio. The
rumor was never confirmed, and police found no evidence of occult
activity in the apartment, Foster said.
   Charity was not ``being held captive'' and appeared to be in
``good physical shape,'' he said.
   The girl was reunited with her mother over the weekend.
</TEXT>
