<HEAD>Omaha World-Herald Endorses Bush For President</HEAD>
<DATELINE>OMAHA, Neb. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The Omaha World-Herald has endorsed Vice
President George Bush over Massachusetts Gov. Michael Dukakis in
their race for the presidency.
   Bush will pursue free trade, less government spending and low
taxes, economic policies that have proven to be effective, the
state's largest newspaper said in an editorial in its Monday
editions.
   In foreign policy, Bush understands and embraces the philosophy
of peace through strength, the newspaper said.
   Dukakis offers domestic proposals that point to more government,
not less, the newspaper said. His defense and foreign policy
proposals point to a more passive, trusting role for the United
States, the newspaper argued.
   The World-Herald also said Bush has more experience than Dukakis.
