   Key:
   BydKEN: Harry Byrd and John F. Kennedy.
   KEN: John F. Kennedy.
   Nixon or NIXON: Richard M. Nixon.
   Unplgd: State carried by unpledged Democratic electors who later
backed Harry Byrd.
   JOHN: Lyndon B. Johnson.
   Gold: Barry Goldwater.
   Humph: Hubert Humphrey.
   Walla: George Wallace.
   McGvr: George McGovern.
   Ford: Gerald R. Ford.
   CART or Cart: Jimmy Carter.
   REAG: Ronald W. Reagan.
   Mond: Walter F. Mondale.
   a: Democrats Byrd and Kennedy shared electoral votes. Byrd got
six of Alabama's 11 electoral votes, Kennedy got the remaining five.
   b: D.C. got electoral votes under 23rd Amendment to the
Constitution, ratified in 1961. It was not included in the 1960
vote.
   c: Byrd won all of Mississippi's eight electoral votes when the
state was carried by unpledged Democratic electors who later
supported him.
   d: Nixon split electoral votes with Byrd. Nixon got seven of
Oklahoma's eight electoral votes, Byrd got the other one.
   e: Nixon split electoral votes with Wallace. Nixon got 12 of
North Carolina's 13 electoral votes, Wallace got the other one.
   f: Nixon split electoral votes with John Hospers. Nixon got 11
of Virginia's 12 electoral votes, Hospers got the other one.
   g: Ford split electoral votes with Reagan. Ford got eight of
Washington state's nine electoral votes, Reagan got the other one.
</TEXT>
