<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Consumer prices rose a moderate 0.3 percent in
September, the smallest gain in three months, as a steep drop in
gasoline costs offset higher food and clothing prices, the
government reported.
   The increase announced Friday in the Labor Department's Consumer
Price Index meant consumer prices were rising at a moderate annual
rate of 4.1 percent last month, down from an annual rate of 5.2
percent in August.
</TEXT>
<DATELINE>MADRID, Spain (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   OPEC members who ended three days of talks
over the weekend agreed the cartel should maintain its crude oil
output at current levels and not increase it until the group
reaches a new agreement on production, the oil minister of Algeria
said.
   The Algerian representative, Balkacem Nabi, said Sunday some of
the eight ministers at last week's meeting asked several OPEC
members to reduce their output but were refused.
